x25CST2WayLgclChanNum.description: This number uniquely identifies the two-way logical channel number to be used in the DTE/DCE interface when establishing an SVC on this interface.

x25CSTPktSeqNumFlg.name: x25CSTPktSeqNumFlg
x25CSTPktSeqNumFlg.description: This parameter allows the user to switch between Basic (modulo 8) and Extended (modulo 128) Packet Sequence Numbering. A value of mod8(1) indicates the use of Basic numbering, while a value of mod128(4) specifies Extended numbering.

x25CSTFlowCntrlNeg.name: x25CSTFlowCntrlNeg
x25CSTFlowCntrlNeg.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable flow control negotiation on this interface. If the value is disable (0), the values of window size and packet size are the specified default values. If the value is enable (1), then this DTE offers its negotiation values and these may be negotiated downwards by the remote entity.

x25CSTDefaultWinSize.name: x25CSTDefaultWinSize
x25CSTDefaultWinSize.description: This is the window size used if Negoriation is not enabled. If basic frame numbering is in operation, then it cannot have a value greater than 7. If extended frame numbering is enabled, then it can have a value up to 127.

x25CSTDefaultPktSize.name: x25CSTDefaultPktSize
x25CSTDefaultPktSize.description: This is the packet size used if Negotiation is not enabled. This must be less than or equal to the Physical Block size on the device.

x25CSTNegWinSize.name: x25CSTNegWinSize
x25CSTNegWinSize.description: This is the window size requested when a connection is being initialised, if Negotiation is enabled. If basic frame numbering is in operation, then it cannot have a value greater than 7. If extended frame numbering is enabled, then it can have a value up to 127.

x25CSTNegPktSize.name: x25CSTNegPktSize
x25CSTNegPktSize.description: This is the packet size requested at call setup time, if Negotiation is enabled. This should not be larger than the Physical Block size defined for this device.

x25CSTCUGSub.name: x25CSTCUGSub
x25CSTCUGSub.description: This parameter allows the enabling of the Closed User Group (CUG) selection facitily for connections on this interface. A Set Request with a value of cugOnly(4) enables Closed User Group operation whilst a value of disabled(0) disables it.

x25CSTLclCUGValue.name: x25CSTLclCUGValue
x25CSTLclCUGValue.description: This value is the number which uniquely defines the Closed User Group value to be used within the Closed User Group Selection facility of the call packet.

x25CSTRvrsChrgReq.name: x25CSTRvrsChrgReq
x25CSTRvrsChrgReq.description: When a connection is being set up, this device will reuqest that Reverse Charging of the call be accepted by the remote end, if the value of this parameter is set to enable(1). A Set Request with a value of disabled(0) disabled this feature.

x25CSTRvrsChrgAcc.name: x25CSTRvrsChrgAcc
x25CSTRvrsChrgAcc.description: When a connection is being set up, this station will accept reverse charging of the call, initiated by the remote end, if the value of this object is set to enable(1). A Set Request with a value of disabled(0) disabled this feature.

x25ConControlTable.name: x25ConControlTable
x25ConControlTable.description: This table holds configurable data used in controlling each X25 SVC.

x25CCTEntry.name: x25CCTEntry
x25CCTEntry.description: Each entry contains configurable objects allowing the control of the status of the SVC.

x25CCTIndex.name: x25CCTIndex
x25CCTIndex.description: This index defines the interface for which this entry is valid. This index is equivalent to the phySerIfNumber index representing the physical serial interfaces on the device.

x25CCTManualConnect.name: x25CCTManualConnect
x25CCTManualConnect.description: This parameter is used to perform a manual (re)connect of the x.25 SVC, when its value is set to connect(2). A value of noAction(1) is returned in response to Get Requests.

x25CCTManualDisconnect.name: x25CCTManualDisconnect
x25CCTManualDisconnect.description: This parameter is used to perform a manual disconnect of the x.25 SVC, when its value is set to disconnect(2). A value of noAction(1) is returned in response to Get Requests.

x25CCTCfgAutoConRetry.name: x25CCTCfgAutoConRetry
x25CCTCfgAutoConRetry.description: This parameter is used to allow the user to configure whether retries are to take place when an SVC is being established. If the station is under manual control then the actual value of the automatic connect retry flag may be different to this object's value. A Set Request with a value of enabled(1) enables this feature whilst a Set Request with a value od disabled(0) disables it.

x25CCTOperAutoConRetryFlg.name: x25CCTOperAutoConRetryFlg
x25CCTOperAutoConRetryFlg.description: This parameter is the actual operation flag which tells us if automatic connect retry is currently enabled on this station. The value of the x25CCTCfgAutoConRetry object is the last configured value of the automatic connect retry flag. A Set Request with a value of enabled(1) enables this feature whilst a Set Request with a value od disabled(0) disables it.

x25CCTAutoConRetryTimer.name: x25CCTAutoConRetryTimer
x25CCTAutoConRetryTimer.description: This is the retry timer, which defines the delay, in seconds, between consecutive attempts to establish the X25 SVC.

x25CCTMaxAutoConRetries.name: x25CCTMaxAutoConRetries
x25CCTMaxAutoConRetries.description: This defines the maximum no of attempts to set up a single X25 SVC allowed. A value of 0 means there is no limit to the number of retries allowed.

x25CCTCfgTODControl.name: x25CCTCfgTODControl
x25CCTCfgTODControl.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable the time-of-day control mechanism, which can control the time period for which an SVC may be active, between two devices. Setting this object also sets the current operating value of the underlying variable. However, this value survives a reset whereas the current value may not. A Set Request with a value of enabled(1) enables this feature whilst a Set Request with a value od disabled(0) disables it.

x25CCTCurrentTODControl.name: x25CCTCurrentTODControl
x25CCTCurrentTODControl.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable the time-of-day control mechanism, which can control the time period for which an SVC is active. A set to this object only sets the operating value of the underlying variable and does not survive a station reset. A Set Request with a value of enabled(1) enables this feature whilst a Set Request with a value od disabled(0) disables it.

x25CCTTODToConnect.name: x25CCTTODToConnect
x25CCTTODToConnect.description: This parameter defined the time of day at which the time-of-day control mechanism, when enabled, will attempt to establish an SVC to the remote end. If the SVC exists at this time then no action is taken. The format of the time is as follows hhmm where hh is the hour and mm is the minute.

x25CCTTODToDisconnect.name: x25CCTTODToDisconnect
x25CCTTODToDisconnect.description: This parameter defined the time of day at which the time-of-day control mechanism, when enabled, will attempt to disconnect an SVC from the remote end. If the SVC is already disconnected at this time then no action is taken. The format of the time is as follows: hhmm where hh is the hour and mm is the minute.

x25TimerTable.name: x25TimerTable
x25TimerTable.description: This table holds the configurable timers used with each X25 connection (SVC).

x25TTEntry.name: x25TTEntry
x25TTEntry.description: Each entry holds the configurable values of timers and retry limits in operation for each SVC.

x25TTIndex.name: x25TTIndex
x25TTIndex.description: This index defines the interface for which this entry is valid. This index is equivalent to the phySerIfNumber index representing the physical serial interfaces on the device.

x25TTT20Timer.name: x25TTT20Timer
x25TTT20Timer.description: This defines the value of the restart retransmit timer, in seconds.

x25TTT21Timer.name: x25TTT21Timer
x25TTT21Timer.description: This defines the value of the call retransmit timer, in seconds.

x25TTT22Timer.name: x25TTT22Timer
x25TTT22Timer.description: This defines the value of the reset retransmit timer, in seconds.

x25TTT23Timer.name: x25TTT23Timer
x25TTT23Timer.description: This defines the value of the clear retransmit timer, in seconds.

x25TTR20Limit.name: x25TTR20Limit
x25TTR20Limit.description: This defines the maximum value of the restart retransmit count, when operating as a DTE.

x25TTR22Limit.name: x25TTR22Limit
x25TTR22Limit.description: This defines the maximum value of the reset retransmit count, when operating as a DTE.

x25TTR23Limit.name: x25TTR23Limit
x25TTR23Limit.description: This defines the maximum value of the clear retransmit count, when operating as a DTE.

x25StatusTable.name: x25StatusTable
x25StatusTable.description: This table holds status information for each X25 SVC and for each interface.

x25StatusTableEntry.name: x25StatusTableEntry
x25StatusTableEntry.description: Each entry keeps status information on each Interface/SVC.

x25StatusIndex.name: x25StatusIndex
x25StatusIndex.description: This index pertains to the interface/SVC for which this entry is valid.

x25StatusIfStatus.name: x25StatusIfStatus
x25StatusIfStatus.description: This object defines the current status of the interface. More specifically, this is the state of the logical channel number 0, which governs the state of the entire SVC.

x25StatusSVCStatus.name: x25StatusSVCStatus
x25StatusSVCStatus.description: This object defines the current status of the SVC, more specifically, the state of the active logical channel. This object has no meaning if the state of the Interface is not r1PktLevelReady.

x25StatusWinSize.name: x25StatusWinSize
x25StatusWinSize.description: This is the window size in operation for the current SVC. This may be less than the Configured Window sized depending on whether Flow Control is enabled, and the result of the negotiation.

x25StatusPktSize.name: x25StatusPktSize
x25StatusPktSize.description: This is the Packet size in use for the current SVC. This may be less than the Configured values, depending on whether Flow Control is enabled and if negotiation has taken place.

x25StatusCauseLastInClear.name: x25StatusCauseLastInClear
x25StatusCauseLastInClear.description: This object defines the Cause of the Last Incoming Clear Received on this interface. It is in th e form of a bit-map, the values and combinations of which are too numerous to list here. The values may be found by referring to the appropriate section in the X25 PLP standard from CCITT.

x25StatusDiagLastInClear.name: x25StatusDiagLastInClear
x25StatusDiagLastInClear.description: This object defines the Diagnostic of the Last Incoming Clear Received on this interface. It is in the form of a bit-map, the values and combinations of which are too numerous to list here. The values may be found by referring to the appropriate section in the X25 PLP standard from CCITT.

x25StatsTable.name: x25StatsTable
x25StatsTable.description: This table holds all statistical data for each x25 SVC. There are two entries in this table, for a 4942.

x25StatsTableEntry.name: x25StatsTableEntry
x25StatsTableEntry.description: Each entry in the Table includes all the statistical objects for each interface.

x25STSVCIndex.name: x25STSVCIndex
x25STSVCIndex.description: This index pertains to the interface for which this entry is valid.

x25STTxDataPkts.name: x25STTxDataPkts
x25STTxDataPkts.description: This is the number of Data Pkts transmitted on this interface.

x25STRxDataPkts.name: x25STRxDataPkts
x25STRxDataPkts.description: This is the number of Data Pkts received on this interface.

x25STTxConnectReqPkts.name: x25STTxConnectReqPkts
x25STTxConnectReqPkts.description: This is the number of Connect Request packets transmitted on this interface.

x25STRxIncomingCallPkts.name: x25STRxIncomingCallPkts
x25STRxIncomingCallPkts.description: This is the number of incoming Call request packets received on this interface.

x25STTxClearReqPkts.name: x25STTxClearReqPkts
x25STTxClearReqPkts.description: This is the number of Clear Request packets transmitted on this interface.

x25STRxClearIndPkts.name: x25STRxClearIndPkts
x25STRxClearIndPkts.description: This is the number of Clear Indication packets received on this interface.

x25STTxResetReqPkts.name: x25STTxResetReqPkts
x25STTxResetReqPkts.description: This is the number of Reset Request packets transmitted on this interface.

x25STRxResetIndPkts.name: x25STRxResetIndPkts
x25STRxResetIndPkts.description: This is the number of Reset Indication packets received on this interface.

x25STTxRestartReqPkts.name: x25STTxRestartReqPkts
x25STTxRestartReqPkts.description: This is the number of Restart Request packets transmitted on this interface.

x25STRxRestartIndPkts.name: x25STRxRestartIndPkts
x25STRxRestartIndPkts.description: This is the number of Restart Indication packets received on this interface.
